In a small bowl, combine dates with boiling water. Set aside to cool. Pre heat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch pan. In a medium bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Set aside. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs. Add flour mixture alternating with cooled date mixture. Fold in chopped nuts and 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips to mixture. Spread batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of chocolate chips over top. Bake in preheated oven for 45 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into middle of cake comes out clean.